rComments: I found Natalia to be a decent lecturer although I found that she was a little too fast in the topics that were new and the topics that were review from high school were somewhat slow. Sometimes boring, but got the job done and gave decent understand to all concepts and the evaluations were fair and based on taught material.

rComments: Natalia is good in A level classes, but killed me in B42. Her lecture structure is confusing and she tends to use examples that aren't relevant. So take at your own risk. In addition, her test/homework questions are worded in an inconsistent way.

She's an ok prof, I don't like her teaching too much. BUT, she's definitely the nicest prof you'll have in first year in terms of MARKS. She gives you lots of extra marks and will literally replace ur midterm with final if you did better. Also she video tapes the lectures so u can watch at home. All in all, very nice prof, not to good at teaching

Quizzes/assignments do NOTHING to prepare you for the exams; the questions on the midterm were SO much harder than the ones we practiced with. I found her explanations to be rather lacking too, often leaving you to interpret long and confusing solutions by ourselves. So far I've been learning everything off of YouTube; I'm definitely dropping soon.

A professor that is very clear on what is taught and expected of the students. Although lectures may contain few arithmetic errors, they do not affect the overall quality of lectures. Also, complete lecture notes are online as well as web videos.

Most generous prof. Gives lots of bonuses and curves as well. Accent might be hard to understand to some. In my year she gave weboption as well. Ended with a 100 in the course when without bonuses or curves I should have probably gotten 85.

She really does try to help her students by having weboption and posting her lecture notes online weekly. Her midterm and final exams are almost the exact same ones as the past ones that she posts with solutions!! She also uploads sample quizzes which is very similar to the quizzes we get in tutorial. She also gives easy bonus questions on final!!
She is so nice. She gives perfect and clear lectures. She really teaches very well! If you do the assignment on time carefully I think theres no problem to get at least 80 in each quiz or test.

She is the nicest prof I've had yet. Her assessments are based off mostly off her lecture notes so if you study those you are good. She posts her lecture notes online and has weboption. I'd still recommend going to lectures and trying to understand what she is doing right away. To top it all off she gives 30 bonus marks on the final and mid term.

Going into this course I was fairly scared of uni calc, however Natalia was very good at reinforcing the basics. Overall it was a lot of work, but there's enough resources in-campus to help you out. Invest in the solution manual if you can, study examples from lectures, and try to keep your mark up so that the final won't make or break your mark.
Nice prof and caring!

She is a really good prof, teaches very clearly with good examples and home questions. Will help you a lot if you see her in her office hours too! Especially before the exams. Really good prof!! Keep up with the course to do well!
good prof but needs you t work more outside class. With a little accent but fair enough to be understood correctly. Recommend!

Dr. Breuss is one of the best professors I've had in my first year at UTSC. Her lectures are amazing and have inspired me to continue on with mathematics.
